  "text": "Rather than conceptualizing attachment as a mediator, [CITATION_1] examined the idea that attachment style moderates the effect of family aggression on dating behavior. That is, they proposed that the relation between aggression in the two contexts differs depending on the quality of adolescents' attachment. The findings supported this hypothesis:",
